srpIfEntry.name: srpIfEntry
srpIfEntry.description: There exists one such entry for every interface in the ifTable which has an ifType of SRP interface (151) Each of these entries are indexed by the value of ifIndex as defined in RFC2233.

srpPriorityThreshold.name: srpPriorityThreshold
srpPriorityThreshold.description: The priority threshold value to be compared against the 3 bits of priority contained in each packet's SRP header. If a packet's priority is greater or equal to this threshold, that packet should be placed in the high priority transmit or transit queue. If a packet's priority is less than this threshold, it should be placed in the low priority transmit or transit queue. Since there are only two types of priority queues (High Priority and Low Priority) a packet is treated as either low or high priority once it is on the ring. Each node determines the threshold value for classifying what is considered a high priority packet and what is considered a low priority packet.

srpNodesOnTheRing.name: srpNodesOnTheRing
srpNodesOnTheRing.description: The number of nodes in the SRP ring. When interface is down the value is 0.

srpIpsState.name: srpIpsState
srpIpsState.description: Each node in the Intelligent Protection Switching (IPS) is one of the following states. Idle - In this mode the node is ready to perform protection and it sends to both neighboring nodes idle IPS messages, which include self in the source address field {0, SELF, 0, S}. PassThrough - Node participate in a protection switch by passing the wrapped traffic and long path signalling through itself. This state is entered based on received IPS messages. Wrapped - Node participate in a protection switch with a wrap present. This state is entered based on protection request issued locally or based on received IPS messages. When interface is down the value for IPS state is passThrough.

srpIpsLockedOut.name: srpIpsLockedOut
srpIpsLockedOut.description: The boolean flag to indicate node LockedOut of protection state. If it's true than Intelligent Protection Swiching is disabled and the node will not wrap on either side of the interface.

srpIpsWaitToRestoreTimer.name: srpIpsWaitToRestoreTimer
srpIpsWaitToRestoreTimer.description: Indicates the length of time in seconds, to remain in the wrap state, after the cause of a wrap is removed. This mechanism prevents protection switch oscillations. Default value is 60 sec.

srpIfTimeElapsed.name: srpIfTimeElapsed
srpIfTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds, including partial seconds, that have elapsed since the beginning of the current measurement interval as described in RFC 2493. If, for some reason, such as an adjustment in the system's time-of-day clock, the current interval exceeds the maximum value, the agent will return the maximum value.

srpIfValidIntervals.name: srpIfValidIntervals
srpIfValidIntervals.description: The number of previous 15-minute measurement intervals for which data was collected. A SRP interface must be capable of supporting at least n intervals. The minimum value of n is 4. The default of n is 32. The maximum value of n is 96. The value will be <n> unless the measurement was (re-)started within the last (<n>*15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals for which the agent has at least some data. In certain cases (e.g., in the case where the agent is a proxy) it is possible that some intervals are unavailable. In this case, this interval is the maximum interval number for which data is available.

srpMACSideTable.name: srpMACSideTable
srpMACSideTable.description: A table of information about the sides of SRP interfaces.

srpMACSideEntry.name: srpMACSideEntry
srpMACSideEntry.description: A list of information specific to a particular side of a particular SRP interface.

srpMACInterfaceSide.name: srpMACInterfaceSide
srpMACInterfaceSide.description: An indication of the side of the interface for which this row contains information.

srpMACNeighborAddress.name: srpMACNeighborAddress
srpMACNeighborAddress.description: The MAC's neighbor's 48-bit individual MAC address.

srpMACSideWrapped.name: srpMACSideWrapped
srpMACSideWrapped.description: The boolean flag to indicate the node's wrapped state.

srpMACIpsMgmtRequestedMode.name: srpMACIpsMgmtRequestedMode
srpMACIpsMgmtRequestedMode.description: The IPS mode requested by management for the local node that can affect the srpMACIpsActiveMode state of the SRP node, according to the set of rules describing IPS protocol. This variable value is one from the following subset (noRequest, manualSwitch, forcedSwitch).

srpMACIpsAutoDetectMode.name: srpMACIpsAutoDetectMode
srpMACIpsAutoDetectMode.description: The current IPS mode as automatically detected by the the local node that can affect the srpMACIpsActiveMode state of the SRP node, according to the set of rules describing IPS protocol. This variable value is one from the following subset (SignalFail, SignalDegrade, WaitToRestore).

srpMACIpsRemoteMode.name: srpMACIpsRemoteMode
srpMACIpsRemoteMode.description: The IPS mode indicated in IPS messages being received by the local node from other nodes on the ring, that can affect the srpMACIpsActiveMode state of the SRP node, according to the set of rules describing IPS protocol.

srpMACIpsRemoteType.name: srpMACIpsRemoteType
srpMACIpsRemoteType.description: Indicates if srpMACIpsRemoteMode object value belongs to the adjacent node in the case of the shortPath or belongs to the non-adjacent node in the case of the longPath.

srpMACIpsActiveMode.name: srpMACIpsActiveMode
srpMACIpsActiveMode.description: The currently active IPS mode for the local node, which can be changed based on combined effect of the following variables: srpMACIpsMgmtRequestedMode, srpMACIpsAutoDetectMode, srpMACIpsRemoteMode, and srpMACIpsRemoteType according to the set of rules describing IPS protocol.

srpMACIpsWrapCounter.name: srpMACIpsWrapCounter
srpMACIpsWrapCounter.description: The number of transition from unwrap to wrap state.

srpMACIpsLastWrapTimeStamp.name: srpMACIpsLastWrapTimeStamp
srpMACIpsLastWrapTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime for the last wrap.

srpMACIpsLastUnWrapTimeStamp.name: srpMACIpsLastUnWrapTimeStamp
srpMACIpsLastUnWrapTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime for the last unwrap.

srpMACClockSourceMode.name: srpMACClockSourceMode
srpMACClockSourceMode.description: Indicates the mode of the SRP interface clock source. Internal - mode specifies the clock source as internal, and is used when connecting between two routers over a dark fiber or over WDM system. The internal mode is used as a default value. Line - mode specifies the clock source as line, and is used when connecting a router to SONET/SDH ADM.

srpMACTopologyTimer.name: srpMACTopologyTimer
srpMACTopologyTimer.description: Indicates the topology-timer on a SRP ring, how frequently topology discovery messages are sent around ring to identify the nodes. Toplogy discovery is always on. The default value is 10 seconds.

srpRingTopologyMapTable.name: srpRingTopologyMapTable
srpRingTopologyMapTable.description: A list of SRP ring topology map entries.

srpRingTopologyMapEntry.name: srpRingTopologyMapEntry
srpRingTopologyMapEntry.description: A MAC entry containing information specific to a particular node on the ring.

srpNodeHopsNumber.name: srpNodeHopsNumber
srpNodeHopsNumber.description: A value, between 0 and (srpNodesOnTheRing - 1), used to identify the particular node which is the number of hops around the ring (clock-wise) away from the local node.

srpNodeMACAddress.name: srpNodeMACAddress
srpNodeMACAddress.description: The node MAC's 48-bit individual MAC address.

srpNodeWrapped.name: srpNodeWrapped
srpNodeWrapped.description: Indicates in general if the node is wrapped without specifying on which side.

srpNodeName.name: srpNodeName
srpNodeName.description: The node name reported by the SRP protocol. If the name is not known then this field is left blank.

srpMACCountersTable.description: The MAC layer traffic Counters table.

srpMACCountersEntry.name: srpMACCountersEntry

srpMACSourceDiscontTimeStamp.name: srpMACSourceDiscontTimeStamp
srpMACSourceDiscontTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion when there was a change in the value of the corresponding instances of either srpMACCountPktsBySourceAddress or srpMACCountPktsBySourceFlag.

srpMACCountPktsBySource.name: srpMACCountPktsBySource

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of srpMACSourceDiscontTimeStamp.

srpMACCountPktsByDestinationFlag.name: srpMACCountPktsByDestinationFlag

srpMACCountPktsByDestAddress.name: srpMACCountPktsByDestAddress

srpMACDestDiscontTimeStamp.name: srpMACDestDiscontTimeStamp
srpMACDestDiscontTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion when there was a change in the value of the corresponding instances of either srpMACCountPktsByDestAddress or srpMACCountPktsByDestinationFlag.

srpMACCountPktsByDest.name: srpMACCountPktsByDest

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of srpMACDestDiscontTimeStamp.

srpMACRejectPktsBySourceFlag.name: srpMACRejectPktsBySourceFlag
